Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.graph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Edge
    An interface that represents a directed edge in a graph.
    Node
    An interface that represents a vertex in a graph.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DocumentGraph
    Represents a Document content as a directed graph where the nodes are SurfaceElement objects and the edges between the nodes are SynDependency objects.
    DummyEdge
    Represents a dummy edge, which is not derived from a SynDependency.
    DummyNode
    Represents a dummy node, which can be used to represent units that go beyond textual units, such as documents, sentences, quotations, etc.
    GraphUtils
    Contains generic static utility methods for graphs created with JGraph.
    SemanticGraph
    Represents the semantic content of a Document as a directed graph where the nodes are Term objects and the edges between the nodes represent roles.
    SentenceGraph
    Represents a sentence-bound portion of a DocumentGraph.
